response.original_title: The Beatles in Washington D.C. - Feb. 11th, 1964
response.overview: THE BEATLES WASHINGTON, D.C. was the first show performed by the most celebrated group in music history during their first visit to the United States in 1964, It captures the magic and excitement surrounding THE BEATLES and features the Fab Four swinging live at the height of Beatlemania.
